  "version": "0.3.0",
  "name": "FIESTA Scattering Bio — scattering transforms complement a plankton CNN",
  "description": "Demonstrates that deterministic Cross Scattering Transform features (FOSCAT, NORIENT=8, RGB, 246-dim) carry information complementary to a fine-tuned ImageNet CNN on plankton classification. Runs on Decrop et al. 2025's open FlowCam dataset and held-out splits. A stacked logistic regression meta-classifier, trained on val.txt and evaluated on test.txt, improves per-class recall on 33 of 95 plankton taxa and lifts rare-class mean recall from 47.7% to 56.1% (+8.4 pp) at a cost of 0.72 pp in overall top-1 accuracy. Part of the FIESTA-OSCARS cross-domain scattering transforms demonstration.",
